==Turkish==
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|tr|/jaz/}}
===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|tr|ota|یاز|tr=yaz}}, from {{der|tr|otk|𐰕𐰖|tr=y¹z||summer}}, from {{der|tr|trk-pro|*yāŕ}} (compare {{cog|cv|ҫур||spring}}, {{cog|sah|саас||spring}}, {{cog|tyv|час||spring}}, {{cog|kk|жаз||summer}}. Compare {{cog|hu|nyár||summer}}, a possible r-Turkic (Bulgar) borrowing).<ref>{{R:tut-pro:SDM}}: [http://starling.rinet.ru/cgi-bin/response.cgi?single=1&basename=%2fdata%2falt%2faltet&text_number=1476&root=config “*ni̯ā́ŕà”]</ref>
====Noun====
{{tr-noun|ı|lar}}
# [[summer]]
=====Usage notes=====
* Locative "yazda" is never or rarely used; instead, use "yazın" to say "in summer".
=====Declension=====
{{tr-infl-noun-c|a|poss=1}}
=====Antonyms=====
* {{l|tr|kış}}
